CatDescriptText: Mrs. Lula Miller, day worker, 310 Morgan Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 3, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Who do you think is responsible for the failure to pass effective civil rights legislation in Congress?"  Answer reads: "It looks like it is the President. He's the top man and therefore he's the one to see that the law passes."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lula Miller wearing eyeglasses and dark button down belted dress with light colored trim on neckline and cuffs, carrying shopping bag, holding light colored handkerchief, standing in front of brick building with windows
